<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<!--@import "_head.kit"-->

<body>
    <!--@import "_header.kit"-->

    <main>
        <article class="project-detail">
            <header class="project-detail-hero section-fade">
                <div class="container narrow">
                    <a href="/portfolio.html" class="back-link">Back to portfolio</a>
                    <p class="eyebrow">Project One</p>
                    <h1>MOVA: Optimizing the In-Store Installment Financing Journey</h1>
                    <p class="lead">A professional case focused on improving an assisted sales flow used by store
                        operators to offer financial products in a retail environment. The work combined journey
                        mapping, behavioral funnel analysis, operator research, business rules and cross-functional
                        collaboration to simplify a complex financial decision.</p>
                </div>
            </header>

            <section class="project-media-section">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="project-cover project-cover-one project-cover-wide"></div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="project-body-section">
                <div class="container detail-grid">
                    <div class="detail-content">
                        <h2>Overview</h2>
                        <p>In Brazil, department store credit cards operate as more than payment instruments. They are
                            connected to credit, insurance, loyalty and financial services. Inside this ecosystem, the
                            store operator plays a key role: explaining the offer, handling objections and helping the
                            customer make a real-time financial decision.</p>
                        <p>The problem was not just interface complexity. It was a B2B2C service experience involving
                            the customer, the operator, the retailer and the bank. The journey needed to become simpler
                            without losing trust, clarity or control.</p>
                        <p><strong>How might we</strong> make the installment payment flow simpler and more efficient
                            for operators, without losing clarity for customers in a debt-restructuring moment?</p>
                        <h2>Process</h2>
                        <p>I contributed across the research, analysis and journey optimization process. My work
                            included mapping the physical journey inside Magalu stores and the digital journey inside
                            the assisted channel, using behavioral funnel analysis to identify friction points and
                            observing how operators interacted with the platform in real sales contexts.</p>

                        <p> I also supported stakeholder interviews, business rules mapping and cross-functional
                            alignment with Product, BI, Design and Commercial teams. The solution focused on reducing
                            unnecessary steps, improving clarity in key decision moments and aligning the interface with
                            the reality of assisted sales.</p>
                    </div>
                    <aside class="project-facts">
                        <h2>Details</h2>
                        <dl>
                            <dt>Date</dt>
                            <dd>September 2024</dd>
                            <dt>Team</dt>
                            <dd>9 members</dd>
                            <dt>Context</dt>
                            <dd>Professional</dd>
                            <dt>Role</dt>
                            <dd>Product Analyst / Journey Mapping / Funnel Analysis / Research / Business Rules Mapping</dd>
                            <dt>Methods:</dt>
                            <dd>Journey Mapping, Google Analytics, Shadowing, Stakeholder Interviews, Service Design, Funnel Analysis</dd>
                            <dt>Impact indicators:</dt>
                            <dd>SLA time, experience checklist, reduced journey screens, pilot completion rate</dd>
                        </dl>
                    </aside>
                </div>
            </section>
        </article>
    </main>

    <!--@import "_footer.kit"-->
</body>

</html>